	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 2nd 1:52 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I read through quite a few pages worth of posts and didn't notice anyone mention some of the spells that Beastlords are lacking.&nbsp;&nbsp;For example, Chloroplast at level 55, but no Regeneration at a lower level.  Alacrity, but no Quickness.  I do feel this would make us even stronger solo, however as far as grouping goes, having some form of haste would definitely make us even more of an asset.  I don't really see how allowing us the Levitate spell would unbalance things either.<br><br>Regarding warder levels, similar to mage and necro pets, the level of the pet buff is not going to be equal to the level of the pet.  The level 60 pet buff Spirit of Khati Sha does not give you a level 60 pet, the warder is lvl 47.  Refer to spell lists on this site to see all the warder max levels.  And no, the Beastlord epic doesn't summon an Epic Warder.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101793435466048></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101793435466048><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=15&mid=101793435466048>RE: Beastlord Spell omissions and warder levels</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=15&mid=101793435466048#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=150941><span id= >ZaymotSilver</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 4th 10:37 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&quot;Regarding warder levels, similar to mage and necro pets, the level of the pet buff is not going to be equal to the level of the pet. The level 60 pet buff Spirit of Khati Sha does not give you a level 60 pet, the warder is lvl 47.&quot;<br><br>My main is a 47th Mage and I have several friends of 50+ level and a friend with a Epic Pet too.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Epic Pet which is &quot;suppose&quot; to be the end all pet for the mage is only 47th level itself.  So I do not see what the problem is.  A 60th BST pet will be the same level as a Mage's Epic Pet, what else do you want?  As for the spells we lack...we are a combat/caster hybrid.  What we lack in spells we make up with our pet and tanking ability.  True there are a few things I would like to see us BSTs get (like more offense and defense skills) but we are STILL a new class.  Its taken VI/Sony almost 2 years to fianlly get to the casters to start balancing, so it may take them another almost 3 years to get the BST class ironed out.  In other words, have a bit of patients and enjoy the class as it currently is and take the nerfs and patches with a grain of salt.<br><br>Sincerely,<br><br>Braxtor<br>30th BST, Fennin Ro<br>Order of the Wolf<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
