	   <tr><td colspan=2>You get a pet summoning ability at lvl 9 and spells also.<br><br>I suggest buying all your spells at lvl 8 and having them with you. When you *DING* lvl 9 sit down and watch your mana bar magically come alive.<br>Mem all your spells (some come from the Shaman guild) and then stand up check your abilities list for your new &quot;summon warder&quot;, make it a hotkey and press it. Summoning yer warder requires no mana.<br><br>Cast &quot;spirit of Sharik&quot; on your pet and watch it get a little bigger (thank god!)<br><br>Poof instant pet. <br>To kill your pet click on the purple icon in your buffs window.<br><br>Some of the pet commands are:<br>/pet kill&nbsp;&nbsp;(pet attacks target)<br>/pet as you were  (cancels previous pet orders-doesnt work well when pet is already attacking )<br>/pet sit<br>/pet stand<br>/pet follow<br>/pet guard here<br><br>there are more...<br><br>Also I suggest using &quot;inner fire&quot; to heal yourself instead of healing.<br><br>For future reference this and a lot more info is available on this website and many others.<br>Also try <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/" target=_new>http://eq.castersrealm.com/</a><br><br>Lucana <br>Barbarian Beastlord<br>Cazic Thule<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Mar 21 13:56:54 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Hobenroby<br>Halfling Druid<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
