	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was also thinking about this too.&nbsp;&nbsp;In my honest opionion, going along with the &quot;wild-man&quot; theme that the Beastlord invokes, it would only make sense for them to track.<br><br>I mean, think about it.  You are supposed to live off the land, make your clothes, weapons, and meals from the beasts of the land.  If your survival rested on being able to find the beasts of the land, wouldndn't it make sense for you to be able to track them down.  In fiction it would be through some heightened sense, knowledge of the land, and natural instinct.  This is in no way reflected by Verant's current BL set up.<br><br>The only way to do this, and perhaps make it quite cool, would be to make it a pet command.<br><br>/pet track X<br><br>Your pet could be like your bloodhound.  just type in the name of the mob you are tracking and watch your pet make a beline for it and rip it to shreds.<br><br>This way it would not be as encompassing as the Ranger, Druid, or Bard track, but still give BL's a more distinct flavor, and make them more dependent on their pets.<br><br>I would also like to see special skill attacks like monks get.  &quot;tiger claw&quot; &quot;gator bite&quot; &quot;bear hug&quot;(with short stun) &quot;wolf kick&quot;  things like this would realy make the BL class a bit more distinct and still keep balance.<br>&nbsp;<br>Sokhota Swordsaint<br>The Sword of Tunare<br>Paladin of 36 Sigils<br>The Nameless</td></tr>
